## use the # No. of genes in the cnts.edger matrix
sim_plotcounts <- function(genenumber) {
    plot(as.integer(group.plot) + runif(ncol(cnts.edger), -0.1, 
        0.1), cnts.edger[genenumber, ], xlim = c(0.5, length(levels(group.plot)) + 
        0.8), xaxt = "n", xlab = "Groups", ylab = "Normalized Counts", 
        main = res.edger[genenumber, ]$Symbol)
    axis(1, at = seq_along(levels(group.plot)), levels(group.plot))
    ## pos below
    text(length(levels(group.plot)) + 0.5, stats::quantile(cnts.edger[genenumber, 
        ], 0.95), paste("log2 Fold Change:", round(res.edger[genenumber, 
        ]$logFC, 2), "", "Adjusted p-value:", format(res.edger[genenumber, 
        ]$FDR, digits = 2, scientific = TRUE), "", "Gene_ID: ", 
        rownames(cnts.edger)[genenumber], sep = "\n"), pos = 1)
}
## plot top 10
for (i in order(res.edger$PValue)[1:10]) {
    sim_plotcounts(i)
}

de_scatter <- function(de, label_fdr, label_fc, name) {
    ggplot(de, aes(logFC, -log10(FDR))) + geom_point(colour = "gray65") + 
        geom_point(data = subset(de, FDR < 0.05 & logFC > 0), 
            aes(logFC, -log10(FDR)), colour = "black") + geom_point(data = subset(de, 
        FDR < 0.05 & logFC < 0), aes(logFC, -log10(FDR)), colour = "gray35") + 
        labs(x = expression(paste(log[2], " Fold Change")), y = expression(paste("-", 
            log[10], " FDR")), caption = paste("Differential Expression Results of ", 
            name)) + geom_text_repel(data = subset(de, FDR < 
        label_fdr & logFC > label_fc), aes(label = Symbol), size = 3, 
        box.padding = unit(0.35, "lines"), point.padding = unit(0.3, 
            "lines")) + geom_hline(yintercept = -log10(0.05), 
        linetype = "dashed", color = "black") + geom_vline(xintercept = 0, 
        linetype = "dashed", color = "black") + annotate(geom = "text", 
        x = 3, y = -log10(0.01), label = "FDR < 0.05", color = "black") + 
        xlim(-1.5, 3.5) + theme_bw()
    
}


de_scatter(isgs_DE, 1e-05, 2, "Core ISGs")

de_scatter(genesbeta_DE, 1e-05, 2, "IFN-Beta Genes")

p1 <- de_scatter(isgs_DE, 1e-05, 2, "Core ISGs")
p2 <- de_scatter(genesbeta_DE, 1e-05, 2, "IFN-Beta Genes")
grid.newpage()

## do pca and get some plots for the data (matrix) The data is

## pheno

prcomp_wrapper <- function(data, gene_symbol, pheno, name) {
    ####### default groups ##############
    group_labels = c("Healthy Controls", "HIV-Infected")
    ###### PCA by prcomp ##########
    data.pca = prcomp(t(data), center = TRUE, scale. = TRUE, 
        retx = TRUE)
    data.pca.symbol = data.pca$rotation
    row.names(data.pca.symbol) = gene_symbol
    data.pca.symbol = as.matrix(data.pca.symbol)
    ########## pc names ##############
    pc_sample = data.frame(data.pca$x)
    pc = colnames(data.pca$x)
    ######### variance of pcs############
    data.sd = (data.pca$sdev/sum(data.pca$sdev)) * 100
    # data for bar plot
    pc.sd = data.frame(PCs = pc, Variance = data.sd) %>% top_n(n = 9, 
        wt = Variance)
    
    p.var = ggplot(data = pc.sd, aes(x = PCs, y = Variance)) + 
        geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "Black") + labs(y = "% Variance", 
        caption = paste("Variance of PCs for ", name)) + theme_bw()
    print(p.var)
    ########### pc1 vs pc2 #############
    pca12 = ggplot(data = pc_sample, aes(x = PC1, y = PC2, color = pheno$txt, 
        shape = pheno$txt)) + geom_point(size = 2) + xlab(paste("PC1 (", 
        round(pc.sd$Variance[1], 2), "%", ")", sep = "")) + ylab(paste("PC2 (", 
        round(pc.sd$Variance[2], 2), "%", ")", sep = "")) + scale_color_manual(values = c("gray70", 
        "Black"), name = "Groups", labels = group_labels) + scale_shape_manual(values = c(16, 
        17), name = "Groups", labels = group_labels) + stat_ellipse(type = "t", 
        linetype = "solid") + labs(caption = paste("PC1 vs PC2 for ", 
        name)) + theme_bw()
    print(pca12)
    
    pca13 = ggplot(data = pc_sample, aes(x = PC1, y = PC3, color = pheno$txt, 
        shape = pheno$txt)) + geom_point(size = 2) + xlab(paste("PC1 (", 
        round(pc.sd$Variance[1], 2), "%", ")", sep = "")) + ylab(paste("PC3 (", 
        round(pc.sd$Variance[3], 2), "%", ")", sep = "")) + scale_color_manual(values = c("gray70", 
        "Black"), name = "Groups", labels = group_labels) + scale_shape_manual(values = c(16, 
        17), name = "Groups", labels = group_labels) + stat_ellipse(type = "t", 
        linetype = "solid") + labs(caption = paste("PC1 vs PC3 for ", 
        name)) + theme_bw()
    print(pca13)
    
    pca23 = ggplot(data = pc_sample, aes(x = PC2, y = PC3, color = pheno$txt, 
        shape = pheno$txt)) + geom_point(size = 2) + xlab(paste("PC2 (", 
        round(pc.sd$Variance[2], 2), "%", ")", sep = "")) + ylab(paste("PC3 (", 
        round(pc.sd$Variance[3], 2), "%", ")", sep = "")) + scale_color_manual(values = c("gray70", 
        "Black"), name = "Groups", labels = group_labels) + scale_shape_manual(values = c(16, 
        17), name = "Groups", labels = group_labels) + stat_ellipse(type = "t", 
        linetype = "solid") + labs(caption = paste("PC2 vs PC3 for ", 
        name)) + theme_bw()
    print(pca23)
    ############### pc1 vs il-6, ifn-beta ###############
    pc1_clin_1 = ggplot(mapping = aes(x = clinical_order$IL.6, 
        y = pc_sample$PC1)) + labs(x = "IL-6 (pg/ml)", y = paste("PC1 (", 
        round(pc.sd$Variance[1], 2), "%", " Variance", ")", sep = ""), 
        caption = paste("IL-6 (pg/ml) vs PC1 for ", name)) + 
        geom_point(aes(shape = pheno$txt, colour = pheno$txt), 
            size = 2.5) + # geom_smooth(method = 'loess', se = FALSE, colour = 'black')
    # +
    geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, colour = "black") + 
        scale_color_manual(values = c("gray70", "Black"), name = "Groups", 
            labels = group_labels) + scale_shape_manual(values = c(16, 
        17), name = "Groups", labels = group_labels) + theme_bw()
    print(pc1_clin_1)
    
    pc1_clin_2 = ggplot(mapping = aes(x = clinical_order$IFNb, 
        y = pc_sample$PC1)) + labs(x = "IFN-Beta", y = paste("PC1 (", 
        round(pc.sd$Variance[1], 2), "%", " Variance", ")", sep = ""), 
        caption = paste("IFN-Beta vs PC1 for ", name)) + geom_point(aes(shape = pheno$txt, 
        colour = pheno$txt), size = 2.5) + # geom_smooth(method = 'loess', se = FALSE, colour = 'black')
    # +
    geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, colour = "black") + 
        scale_color_manual(values = c("gray70", "Black"), name = "Groups", 
            labels = group_labels) + scale_shape_manual(values = c(16, 
        17), name = "Groups", labels = group_labels) + theme_bw()
    print(pc1_clin_2)
}
